        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "String literals and String which is acted upon intern() method will go in SCP area. Rest all in heap",
        "body": "<p><code>String literals<\/code> and <code>String<\/code> which is acted upon <code>intern()<\/code> method will go in <code>SCP area<\/code>. Rest all in heap.<\/p>\n\n<p>If that is the case if i create <\/p>\n\n<p><code>String s = new String(\"apple\");<\/code> <\/p>\n\n<p>Obviously it will create one object in <code>heap<\/code>, my doubt is it will create \"<code>apple<\/code>\" in <code>SCP(String Constant Pool)<\/code> also. (Lets assume \"apple\" is not there in SCP).<\/p>\n\n<p>What about <code>String[] arrays<\/code>?<\/p>\n\n<p>Can you please elaborate in detail.. <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 25802249,
